cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses a neural network model for sequence learning, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The model is unsupervised and uses Hebbian-like learning, which suggests it may fall under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also compares the model to other sequence learning algorithms, which suggests it may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is applied to sequence prediction problems with both artificial and real-world data, which suggests it may fall under the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and systems and control (cs.SY).
